ympathetic ganglion\nproperty_value: editor_note \"TODO - check\" xsd:string\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0007711\nname: sixth cervical dorsal root ganglion\nsynonym: \"C6 dorsal root ganglion\" EXACT [EMAPA:25159]\nsynonym: \"sixth cervical dorsal root ganglia\" EXACT [FMA:6319]\nsynonym: \"sixth cervical dorsal root ganglion\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:2608]\nsynonym: \"sixth cervical spinal ganglion\" EXACT [FMA:6319]\nxref: BIRNLEX:2608\nxref: EMAPA:25159\nxref: FMA:6319\nis_a: UBERON:0002834 {source=\"NIFSTD\"} ! cervical dorsal root ganglion\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0007712\nname: fourth thoracic spinal ganglion\nsubset: defined_by_ordinal_series\nsynonym: \"fourth thoracic dorsal root ganglion\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:2614, FMA:6324, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\nxref: BIRNLEX:2614\nxref: EMAPA:25177\nxref: FMA:6324\nxref: UMLS:C0501702 {source=\"BIRNLEX:2614\"}\nis_a: UBERON:0002835 {source=\"FMA\"} ! thoracic dorsal root ganglion\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0007713\nname: fourth sacral spinal ganglion\nsynonym: \"forth sacral dorsal root ganglion\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:2631]\nsynonym: \"fourth sacral dorsal root ganglion\" EXACT [FMA:6345, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\nxref: BIRNLEX:2631\nxref: EMAPA:25173\nxref: FMA:6345\nxref: UMLS:C0501723 {source=\"BIRNLEX:2631\"}\nis_a: UBERON:0002837 {source=\"FMA\"} ! sacral dorsal root ganglion\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0016610\nname: nucleus proprius of spinal cord\ndef: \"The Nucleus proprius is a layer of the spinal cord adjacent to the substantia gelatinosa. Nucleus proprius constitutes the bulk of the dorsal horn and receives inputs from the dorsal root ganglions that carry sensory information, such as light touch, as well as pain and temperature information. Cells in this nucleus project to deeper laminae of the spinal cord, to the posterior column nuclei, and to other supraspinal relay centers including the midbrain, thalamus, and hypothalamus. Rexed laminae III, IV, and V make up the nucleus propius Nucleus proprius (NP), along with nucleus dorsalis (ND) are involved in sensing fine touch and proprioception.\" [Wikipedia:Nucleus_proprius_of_spinal_cord]\nsynonym: \"nucleus proprius\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1633, Wikipedia:Nucleus_proprius_of_spinal_cord]\nsynonym: \"nucleus proprius columnae posterioris\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [NeuroNames:1633]\nsynonym: \"nucleus proprius cornu dorsalis\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [NeuroNames:1633]\nsynonym: \"nucleus proprius dorsalis\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [NeuroNames:1633]\nsynonym: \"nucleus proprius medullae spinalis\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [FMA:73906, FMA:TA]\nsynonym: \"nucleus proprius of the spinal cord\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1633]\nsynonym: \"proper sensory nucleus\" EXACT [FMA:73906]\nsynonym: \"proper sensory nucleus\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1633]\nxref: FMA:73906\nxref: neuronames:1633\nxref: Wikipedia:Nucleus_proprius_of_spinal_cord\nis_a: UBERON:0002020 ! gray matter\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002256 ! dorsal horn of spinal cord\n\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
